I'm uncomfortable with the use of `None` as a semaphore for "do nothing." However remote, it seems there could be a possibility of a validator intending to convert a value to `None`. In general, in these kinds of scenarios, I prefer an explicit, unambiguous semaphore, usually passed into the method that might use it:

def _from_base_type(self, value, _nope):
    # Base value to (strict) user value.'
    if not isinstance(value, SomeBaseType):
        return SomeUserType(value)
    return _nope

... but with a better name than `_nope`.  I suspect we're constrained by backwards compatibility considerations on this point, though, so this is probably more for posterity than anything else.

